# üçè Nano Text Editor ‚Äì Shortcut Cheat Sheet (macOS)

## ‚úÖ How to Select and Delete All Text

1. **Go to the start of the file:**
   - `Ctrl + Y` (scroll up) or `Ctrl + _` then enter line `1`

2. **Start selection (set mark):**
   - `Ctrl + ^` *(same as `Ctrl + 6`)*

3. **Go to end of file:**
   - `Ctrl + V` (scroll down)

4. **Delete selected text:**
   - `Ctrl + K` (cut)

To paste again (optional): `Ctrl + U`

---

## üß≠ Navigation & Scrolling

| Shortcut        | Action                          |
|-----------------|----------------------------------|
| `Ctrl + A`       | Move to beginning of line       |
| `Ctrl + E`       | Move to end of line             |
| `Ctrl + Y`       | Scroll up one screen            |
| `Ctrl + V`       | Scroll down one screen          |
| `Ctrl + _`       | Go to specific line             |
| `Ctrl + C`       | Show current cursor position    |

---

## ‚úèÔ∏è Text Editing

| Shortcut        | Action                          |
|-----------------|----------------------------------|
| `Ctrl + K`       | Cut line or selected text       |
| `Ctrl + U`       | Paste previously cut text       |
| `Ctrl + ^`       | Set mark (begin text selection) |
| `Ctrl + T`       | Spell check (if enabled)        |

---

## üíæ File Operations

| Shortcut        | Action                          |
|-----------------|----------------------------------|
| `Ctrl + O`       | Save (write out) file           |
| `Ctrl + X`       | Exit nano                      |
| `Ctrl + G`       | Show help (shortcut guide)      |

---

## üîÑ Undo / Redo (if supported in your nano version)

| Shortcut        | Action                          |
|-----------------|----------------------------------|
| `Alt + U`        | Undo last action                |
| `Alt + E`        | Redo undone action              |

---

## üõ† Notes

- `Ctrl + ^` is the same as pressing `Ctrl + 6`
- `Alt` is typically the `Option` key on macOS
- `^` = Control key, e.g., `^K` = `Ctrl + K`

---

